abindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5565154\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_5565154\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Apr 30, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104nzq1702624284885.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nzq1702624284885.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/nzq1702624284885.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pph1665702773333\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">Configure Indentation in the\n    Script Editor</h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"pph1665702773333__configure_indentation_and_line_numbering_in_the_script_editor_18187\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">By default, the Script Editor is configured to indent code using a tab character that\n    is equivalent to 4 spaces. If your coding standards or preferences call for the use of spaces or\n    a different tab size, you can change this configuration.</p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"pph1665702773333__topic_d4367e1_d4368e1_d4369e1\">\n<div class=\"p\">Uniface provides the following two ways to configure the indentation settings:<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pph1665702773333__ul_gfz_q4r_51c\">\n<li class=\"li\">By adding the formatting subsection in the ASN file</li>\n<li class=\"li\">By modifying the widget properties in the INI file</li>\n</ul></div>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"pph1665702773333__note_ivb_lpr_51c\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> Any settings defined in the ASN file always takes precedence over\n        the widget properties defined in the INI file. We strongly recommend that all developers\n        share the same formatting subsection to maintain code consistency.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"pph1665702773333__section_fnv_npr_51c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d489932e69\">Configuring indentation across multiple installations</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">To configure code indentation for multiple developers, create a formatting subsection in an\n        ASN file, and make sure it is included:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pph1665702773333__pre_u5k_wpr_51c\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;ASN file\n[formatting]\n..\nIndentSize = 2\nIndentTabs = false\n..\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pph1665702773333__ul_m1p_bqr_51c\">\n<li class=\"li\">IndentTabs: Use the tab characters for indentation; one of <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">on</code> (use tabs) or <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code> (use spaces). The\n          default value is <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">on</code>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">IndentSize: The size of the indentation in space characters. The default value is\n            <code class=\"ph codeph\">4</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"pph1665702773333__section_n1p_bqr_51c\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d489932e102\">Configuring indentation for a single installation</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">When code consistency is not a concern, developers can define their preference as a widget\n        property in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">SourceEdit</code> widget.</p>\n<p class=\"p\">The INI file allows the use of <code class=\"ph codeph\">IndentGuides</code>, which shows a visual guide of\n        the indentation. Since this setting does not affect the ProcScript code, it can only be set\n        in the INI file. It cannot be set in the ASN file.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pph1665702773333__p_d4370e1_d4371e1_d4372e1\">To configure code indentation, edit the Script Editor\n        definition in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> file:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"pph1665702773333__pre_gnv_npr_51c\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;usys.ini\n[widgets]\n...\nSourceEdit=usrcedit(font=procboxfont;language=uniface;indenttabs=off;indentsize=2;indentguides=off)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"pph1665702773333__ul_hnv_npr_51c\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pph1665702773333__li_d1763e1_d1764e1_d1765e1\">IndentTab: Use the tab characters for indentation; one\n          of <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">on</code> (use tabs) or <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code> (use\n          spaces). The default value is <code class=\"ph codeph defvalue\">on</code>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pph1665702773333__li_d1766e1_d1767e1_d1768e1\">IndentSize: The size of the indentation in space\n          characters. The default value is <code class=\"ph codeph\">4</code>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"pph1665702773333__li_d1769e1_d1770e1_d1771e1\">IndentGuides: To display indentation guides as vertical\n          lines, the default is <code class=\"ph codeph\">off</code>.</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xeb1665702791582.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Script Editor</a><p>The Script Editor enables you to write ProcScript and JavaScript that controls the behavior of the component.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5565154\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_5565154\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Configure Indentation in the Script Editor Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Apr 30, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Configure Indentation in the Script Editor By default, the Script Editor is configured to indent code using a tab character that is equivalent to 4 spaces. If your coding standards or preferences call for the use of spaces or a different tab size, you can change this configuration. Uniface provides the following two ways to configure the indentation settings: By adding the formatting subsection in the ASN file By modifying the widget properties in the INI file Note: Any settings defined in the ASN file always takes precedence over the widget properties defined in the INI file. We strongly recommend that all developers share the same formatting subsection to maintain code consistency. Configuring indentation across multiple installations To configure code indentation for multiple developers, create a formatting subsection in an ASN file, and make sure it is included: ;ASN file [formatting] .. IndentSize = 2 IndentTabs = false .. Copy IndentTabs: Use the tab characters for indentation; one of on (use tabs) or off (use spaces). The default value is on . IndentSize: The size of the indentation in space characters. The default value is 4 . Configuring indentation for a single installation When code consistency is not a concern, developers can define their preference as a widget property in the SourceEdit widget. The INI file allows the use of IndentGuides , which shows a visual guide of the indentation. Since this setting does not affect the ProcScript code, it can only be set in the INI file. It cannot be set in the ASN file. To configure code indentation, edit the Script Editor definition in the usys.ini file: ;usys.ini [widgets] ... SourceEdit=usrcedit(font=procboxfont;language=uniface;indenttabs=off;indentsize=2;indentguides=off) Copy IndentTab: Use the tab characters for indentation; one of on (use tabs) or off (use spaces). The default value is on . IndentSize: The size of the indentation in space characters. The default value is 4 . IndentGuides: To display indentation guides as vertical lines, the default is off . Related Links Script Editor The Script Editor enables you to write ProcScript and JavaScript that controls the behavior of the component. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}